     <div type="to_the_printer">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To the Printer.</head>
   <p>MY conceite is, that these are very la<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mētable verses, &amp; will greiue many the reading, they so expresse death to life &amp; make mortality immortal; I wish that as many as can make vse of such pittifull lines had copies, the rest may want them: Here and there a verse may occa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sion a teare, then the Author is a true water-Poet indeed, but else where, there wants not an hand-kercheife to dry that teare: So is the whole worke a <gap reason="foreign">
         <desc>〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉</desc>
      </gap> and deserues an approbation at least from</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Io. TAYLOR.</signed>
      <dateline>OR. COLL.</dateline>
   </closer>
</div>
